metadata.name: The Call of the Wild
metadata.description:
When the long winter nights come
And the wolves follow their meat
Into the lowers valleys, he may be seen running at the head of the pack
Through the pale 
Moonlight or glimmering borealis
Leaping gigantic above his fellows
His great throat
A-below as he sing a song of the younger world
Which is the song of the pack
Jack London
